4. a. Proetutianum Hadrianum agrum. Hadria (Atri) lay about five miles from the Adriatic, a little south of the box-ders of the Praetutii. It became a Roman colony B.c. 232, and was one of the eighteen which remained faithful at the most critical period of the war, (xxvii. 10).

b. Arpos. After the battle of Cannae, this city was one of the first to submit to Hannibal, and it continued in his
